    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels way deeper than just a hack though. i feel like my actual \"self\" is being hollowed out. like the thing online is more \"me\" than i am right now because it's always active and always saying the right things. if it has my schedule and my patterns down perfectly... what's stopping it from eventually just replacing me entirely in every way? like, if it's doing a better job at being me than i am, does the original me even matter anymore?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
